See: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html

The shim code in this directory (excluding bundled mautrix/meta and Synapse
binaries) is also licensed AGPL-3.0-or-later to maintain license compatibility
with the aggregate work.

If you run this image as a network service, AGPL §13 requires that you offer
network users the complete corresponding source code. Sources:

- mautrix/meta: https://github.com/mautrix/meta
- Synapse:      https://github.com/matrix-org/synapse
- This shim:    the containing GoClaw repository's `sidecar/mautrix-meta-shim/` directory

GoClaw itself (the gateway that consumes this sidecar via HTTP) is a separate
work that does NOT link any AGPL code. GoClaw communicates with this sidecar
strictly over HTTP between independent processes.
